      "content": "interesting. you say it was a failure, but wouldn't someone argue that the primary goal of the R2P (Responsibility to Protect) framework was just preventing a massacre in Benghazi, which the intervention actually did achieve? isn't that a success in itself regardless of what happened to the state later?",
